Package com.natwest.opendata.service

Class ATMServiceImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.natwest.opendata.service.ATMServiceImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ATMService, BaseOpenDataService<ATM>
    public class ATMServiceImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements ATMService
    The ATMServiceImpl class is an implementaion of ATMSerivce Interface. All methods pertaining to ATM functionalities are implemented in this class.

    ATMServiceImpl is public class, an implementation, that get exposed to the developers or consumer of this SDK. Because ATMServiceImpl is public class, its methods are visible and can be consumed.

    Here are some more examples of how ATM Service can be used: 

         Recommended way to use:
     OpenDataService openDataService=new OpenDataService(Environment.PROD);
      ATMService atmService=openDataService.getAtmService();
      atmService.getAlldata();

    The class ATMSerivceImpl includes methods for consuming various functionalities pertaining to ATMs open data SDK, for example getting all Atms data as list, filtering Atms based on properties such as accessibility, location, postCode and town Name.

    Exposed Methods:

    • getATMsByFilter
    • getAllData
    • exportAllDataAsCSV

      • getATMsByFilter

        public java.util.List<ATM> getATMsByFilter​(@NonNull
                                           @NonNull ATMFilterEnum filterName,
                                           @NonNull
                                           @NonNull java.lang.String filterValue)
        Filters ATM response based on the attributes present in the atm response. filterName specified as the first parameter is the property in ATM response and filterValue specified as the second parameter is the value of that property, against which the filtering is required. This method's return type is list of atm.

        The Items in a list or array is separated by ; instead of , to avoid conflict in csv file

        Specified by:
        getATMsByFilter in interface ATMService
        Parameters:
        filterName - Takes Enum ATMFilterEnum which has various filtering criteria
        filterValue - Takes string, which maps to the property value in ATM service response
        Returns:
        filtered list of ATMs on which criteria are applied.
